WEBVTT

00:39.001 --> 00:44.001
<font color="#808040">Sync & corrections by</font> <font color="#ffff80">Costa Dax</font>
<font color="#008000">www.addic7ed.com</font>

00:47.003 --> 00:49.203
I know you don't want to
hear this, but I have a plan.

00:49.204 --> 00:51.871
You're right, I don't want
to hear it, so let's drop it.

00:56.079 --> 00:59.080
What the fuck did you just do?

00:59.149 --> 01:00.582
That right there

01:00.650 --> 01:02.517
is some of the finest
saffron on the market.

01:02.586 --> 01:05.486
- Saffron?
- You got no idea.

01:05.555 --> 01:07.222
This stuff is like red gold.

01:07.290 --> 01:09.690
It's easily the most expensive
spice by weight on the planet.

01:09.691 --> 01:11.493
And guess where it's grown?

01:11.561 --> 01:14.062
Right here, in the
fertile blood-soaked soil

01:14.131 --> 01:15.497
of Afghanistan.

01:15.565 --> 01:17.132
How convenient.

01:17.200 --> 01:19.400
This stuff sells for like
500 bucks an ounce retail.

01:19.429 --> 01:20.989
Double that in some parts of the world.

01:20.990 --> 01:22.637
We've been wasting
our time with hashish.

01:22.706 --> 01:24.273
Look, whatever you're scheme
you're coming up with next,

01:24.274 --> 01:25.807
I don't want any part of it.

01:25.876 --> 01:27.909
I owe people in four
different time zones money.

01:27.978 --> 01:29.477
A lot of money.

01:29.546 --> 01:31.846
Look, I've already
worked out all the math.

01:31.915 --> 01:34.149
For every pound of
this stuff that we sell,

01:34.217 --> 01:36.317
we make a cool eight grand profit.

01:36.386 --> 01:38.106
Local farmers are already
growing the stuff.

01:38.107 --> 01:40.155
All we gotta do is
buy low and sell high.

01:40.223 --> 01:42.357
- Oh, is that all?
- Yeah.

01:44.227 --> 01:45.927
Perfect.

01:45.996 --> 01:48.596
We sell directly to high-end
restaurants all over the world.

01:48.665 --> 01:51.399
For one, we have no contacts
for high-end restaurants

01:51.468 --> 01:53.201
all over the world.

01:53.270 --> 01:54.969
For two, most of the saffron trade

01:55.038 --> 01:57.172
around these parts is run by Taliban.

01:57.240 --> 01:59.040
And for three, you forgot
to mention the part

01:59.109 --> 02:01.442
where it takes a couple
hundred thousand flowers

02:01.511 --> 02:04.612
just to harvest a single
pound of the stuff.

02:07.450 --> 02:09.150
How do you know all that?

02:09.219 --> 02:11.219
I've been reading the same
article in the "Nat Geo"

02:11.220 --> 02:12.752
that's been sitting on the toilet

02:12.821 --> 02:14.822
for the last two months that you did.

02:14.891 --> 02:17.425
I just happened to
read the entire article.

02:17.994 --> 02:19.894
I'm just trying to help you out, man.

02:19.963 --> 02:21.896
Appreciate it, but all
your schemes so far

02:21.965 --> 02:23.865
were supposed to be a sure thing.

02:23.934 --> 02:26.467
The only thing I know for
sure is that I'm flat broke

02:26.536 --> 02:29.337
and my family is about
to lose their home.

02:29.406 --> 02:31.439
I can't afford any more losses, my man.

02:31.508 --> 02:33.007
We're gonna figure this one out.

02:33.076 --> 02:35.143
We always do.

02:35.212 --> 02:36.978
Can I sit with you guys?

02:38.248 --> 02:39.547
It's not fucking middle school.

02:39.616 --> 02:41.216
You don't need to ask.

02:41.284 --> 02:43.384
I was home schooled.

02:43.453 --> 02:47.589
So did you see those
rad wheels out there?

02:47.657 --> 02:50.458
- Stay away, kid.
- What? Why?

02:50.527 --> 02:51.887
You got a lot better things to do

02:51.888 --> 02:53.661
with the money you don't have.

02:53.730 --> 02:56.030
Okay, but I... I can go look, can't I?

02:56.099 --> 02:57.699
Just don't touch.

02:57.700 --> 02:59.001
Okay.

02:59.402 --> 03:01.703
- Well, you know what?
- Uh, I'm not hungry.

03:01.771 --> 03:05.240
I'm gonna go check 'em out.

03:05.308 --> 03:08.109
Keep it in your pants, kid.

03:09.980 --> 03:12.447
They are beautiful, aren't they?

03:12.515 --> 03:14.482
Don't you think after
laying your life on the line

03:14.551 --> 03:16.017
to spread freedom and democracy,

03:16.086 --> 03:17.726
you deserve to come
home in something nice

03:17.795 --> 03:18.995
waiting for you in the garage?

03:18.996 --> 03:20.855
Well, it's my parents' garage.

03:22.993 --> 03:25.293
Why don't you get in? Fire her up.

03:28.465 --> 03:30.365
I never get tired of that sound.

03:31.735 --> 03:33.434
Now I can get you into this

03:33.503 --> 03:35.570
for a low down payment of $5,000.

03:36.873 --> 03:38.473
Oh, that's a lot of money.

03:38.541 --> 03:39.861
That's barely three months' pay.

03:39.930 --> 03:41.463
It's tax-free, and I'm gonna give you

03:41.531 --> 03:43.444
a $500 military discount.

03:43.513 --> 03:46.481
Close your eyes for
a second. Picture this.

03:46.549 --> 03:49.684
You return home a war hero.

03:49.753 --> 03:52.287
You pull up to a stoplight
in your brand-new sled.

03:52.355 --> 03:55.790
In the car next to you, it's your rival.

03:55.859 --> 03:57.992
- I don't have a rival.
- Light turns green,

03:58.061 --> 04:00.028
you dust that jackalope off the line.

04:00.096 --> 04:03.531
Zero to 60, 3.5 seconds.

04:03.600 --> 04:05.600
Whole town sees it.

04:05.669 --> 04:07.568
Ladies will be literally fighting

04:07.637 --> 04:11.105
over who gets to blow you
from this passenger seat.

04:12.876 --> 04:15.209
Thank you for your work.
Thank you very much.

04:15.278 --> 04:17.345
Thank you. How are you?

04:17.414 --> 04:19.346
Good to see you. Eat up, gentlemen.

04:19.416 --> 04:21.015
As you can see, it's a multiethnic,

04:21.084 --> 04:23.184
multinational base, got
a lot of moving parts,

04:23.253 --> 04:25.173
but they move well together.
That's what matters.

04:25.174 --> 04:27.188
That's attributed to
your fine work as well.

04:27.257 --> 04:29.490
Well, I'm doing the best
I can with what I got.

04:29.559 --> 04:32.460
Ah, thank you.

04:32.529 --> 04:34.028
Staying out of trouble, Sergeant?

04:34.097 --> 04:35.863
Uh, doing my best, sir.

04:35.932 --> 04:38.433
I'm giving Mr. Goodall, the
new Secretary of the Army,

04:38.501 --> 04:40.335
a tour around FOB Guardian.

04:40.403 --> 04:42.837
Oh, welcome to the Orphanage, sir.

04:42.906 --> 04:44.005
The Orphanage?

04:44.074 --> 04:45.373
It's an unsanctioned nickname.

04:45.442 --> 04:46.974
- Ah.
- Yeah, when you're

04:47.043 --> 04:49.143
in a foreign country, out
in the middle of nowhere,

04:49.212 --> 04:50.611
it's easy to feel abandoned.

04:50.680 --> 04:53.247
Orphanage sounds apt. I like it.

04:53.316 --> 04:55.316
Sergeant Alvarez is one
of my best flight medics.

04:55.318 --> 04:56.718
Hm.

04:56.786 --> 04:59.487
Best of luck with this
war, Mr. Secretary.

05:01.758 --> 05:04.559
Maybe let's get a picture
over there, switch things up.

05:07.263 --> 05:10.665
Sergeant, would you mind taking a photo?

05:10.734 --> 05:12.033
Sarah, my executive assistant,

05:12.102 --> 05:15.370
keeps telling me that
I need fresh content

05:15.438 --> 05:17.038
for my social media platforms.

05:17.107 --> 05:18.506
- Sure.
- Milton!

05:18.575 --> 05:20.775
Like to introduce you
all to Allen Milton,

05:20.844 --> 05:22.443
one of the best war photojournalists

05:22.512 --> 05:23.978
who's ever lived.

05:24.047 --> 05:25.480
Yeah, close in up.

05:25.481 --> 05:27.681
Colonel Austin, could
you just... Thanks.

05:27.684 --> 05:30.585
Say "too old for this shit".

05:32.134 --> 05:33.521
Got it? Good.

05:33.590 --> 05:35.390
Sergeant, if there is anything you need,

05:35.458 --> 05:38.025
please feel free to contact my office.

05:38.094 --> 05:40.428
Service members like yourself
keep this machine running.

05:40.497 --> 05:42.530
Sir, can I ask a question?

05:42.599 --> 05:44.232
That's why I'm here.

05:44.300 --> 05:46.634
Why is the DOD terminating
the MAVNI program?

05:46.703 --> 05:48.770
- Alvarez...
- No.

05:48.838 --> 05:50.271
That's an honest question.

05:50.340 --> 05:53.007
And maybe one day we'll
have the time to sit down

05:53.076 --> 05:54.942
so I can give you a complicated answer

05:55.011 --> 05:56.811
to a complicated situation.

05:56.880 --> 05:58.746
Uh, Mr. Secretary,

05:58.815 --> 06:00.782
I wanna show you our
Tactical Operations Center.

06:00.850 --> 06:02.784
- Good idea.
- Terrific.

06:02.852 --> 06:05.319
Mr. Secretary...

06:05.989 --> 06:07.722
Sorry, I realize you're very busy,

06:07.791 --> 06:10.291
but if you had a moment,
my team and I would love

06:10.360 --> 06:11.859
to take you for a spin in the bird.

06:11.928 --> 06:13.428
Show you what it's like to be

06:13.456 --> 06:14.856
a combat medic here in Afghanistan.

06:14.857 --> 06:17.398
That would be very enlightening.

06:17.467 --> 06:20.201
Sarah, follow up with
Colonel Austin's office

06:20.270 --> 06:21.569
to set that up.

06:21.638 --> 06:23.638
Done.

06:27.377 --> 06:30.378
Your crew is hell-bent on
being a pain in my ass!

06:30.447 --> 06:32.327
And may I remind you that
you are still grounded

06:32.348 --> 06:34.682
after that incident with
SecCorp and the morphine?

06:35.718 --> 06:38.553
Stay in your lane,
Sergeant! That's an order!

06:42.240 --> 06:43.806
Way to get us back in the air.

06:43.875 --> 06:45.775
Look, it'll give us a
chance to corner this guy

06:45.776 --> 06:47.310
and maybe change his mind
on this MAVNI bullshit.

06:47.311 --> 06:49.144
'Cause there's no guarantee
that this marriage

06:49.173 --> 06:50.413
is gonna get you the Green Card

06:50.414 --> 06:51.814
and keep you from getting deported.

06:51.849 --> 06:53.609
Nothing is going to change
that man's mind.

06:53.651 --> 06:54.731
We're gonna try.

06:54.786 --> 06:56.826
She's right. Those
motherfuckers tow the party line.

06:56.827 --> 06:58.487
They don't make decisions by themselves.

06:58.556 --> 07:00.316
At least I'll get some
special dispensation

07:00.317 --> 07:01.790
for my wife out of it then.

07:01.859 --> 07:03.979
You will do anything to have
this marriage annulled.

07:11.067 --> 07:12.734
Raise you 50.

07:12.802 --> 07:15.069
- Puts me all in.
- That's the idea.

07:15.138 --> 07:17.305
Call.

07:17.374 --> 07:18.973
You gonna show your hand?

07:19.042 --> 07:20.402
Hang on. What are you doing here?

07:20.443 --> 07:22.076
Why are you ghosting me

07:22.145 --> 07:24.065
like I'm some shitty date
you're trying to shake?

07:24.066 --> 07:25.079
Ghosting?

07:25.148 --> 07:26.814
I think it's what the kids call it

07:26.883 --> 07:28.683
when you don't wanna
talk to someone anymore.

07:28.752 --> 07:30.385
Hey buddy, go fuck yourself.

07:32.422 --> 07:33.902
You know you're not allowed in here.

07:33.903 --> 07:35.670
Try and remove me.

07:40.663 --> 07:42.383
Why did you say "and
that's how you sell it"

07:42.384 --> 07:43.865
to me after the fight?

07:43.933 --> 07:46.033
I was just having a little fun, babe.

07:46.102 --> 07:47.742
- Were you?
- What do you wanna say to me?

07:47.804 --> 07:50.638
- Did you take a dive?
- Huh?

07:50.707 --> 07:52.640
You heard what I said.

07:52.709 --> 07:57.178
During the fight did you take a dive?

07:57.247 --> 07:59.280
Answer the fucking question.

07:59.349 --> 08:00.848
Why would I do that?

08:00.917 --> 08:03.718
That's what I'm here to find out.

08:03.787 --> 08:05.420
How'd Roback know to bet on me?

08:05.488 --> 08:06.988
How the hell do I know?

08:07.056 --> 08:09.176
After I told you all about
the Bodyguard's weakness,

08:09.205 --> 08:10.725
you couldn't wait to run and tell him.

08:10.726 --> 08:11.826
Okay, yes.

08:11.895 --> 08:14.028
I told him because I knew
Davis needed the cash.

08:14.091 --> 08:15.531
He was gonna lose his family's home,

08:15.532 --> 08:16.772
and I knew that could help him.

08:16.773 --> 08:19.467
Bullshit! This isn't about Davis.

08:19.536 --> 08:21.502
This is about Roback.

08:21.571 --> 08:23.331
This is about you screwing
him behind my back

08:23.332 --> 08:25.199
the entire time we've been together.

08:25.809 --> 08:27.308
I'm over Roback.

08:27.377 --> 08:30.578
That doesn't really answer
the question, does it?

08:30.647 --> 08:32.212
It should.

08:32.282 --> 08:34.682
I had a gut feeling that
everything I told you

08:34.751 --> 08:37.083
would get back to
Roback, and I was right.

08:37.153 --> 08:39.352
Wow, so this was some
kind of loyalty test.

08:39.422 --> 08:44.091
- And you failed.
- Well, fuck you and your test.

08:44.794 --> 08:46.794
Then I need to hear it.

08:47.997 --> 08:49.717
Have you been screwing
Roback behind my back

08:49.718 --> 08:51.184
this whole time we've been together?

08:57.974 --> 08:59.173
Fuck!

09:02.545 --> 09:05.446
- Hey.
- Hey, hey.

09:05.515 --> 09:07.014
I was starting to think

09:07.083 --> 09:09.817
I was never gonna hear from you again.

09:09.886 --> 09:11.419
How did Max do in his game?

09:11.488 --> 09:13.855
Good, he hit the game-winning home run.

09:13.923 --> 09:15.289
- Oh!
- Yeah.

09:15.358 --> 09:16.624
He's really killing it.

09:16.693 --> 09:18.059
I mean, the coach is going nuts.

09:18.127 --> 09:20.595
Oh, that's great.

09:21.364 --> 09:24.131
Um...

09:24.200 --> 09:26.067
so my tour got extended by three months.

09:26.135 --> 09:29.270
Are you fucking kidding me? Why?

09:29.339 --> 09:31.038
We're spread so thin,

09:31.107 --> 09:33.441
and, you know, my
job is mission critical.

09:33.510 --> 09:36.143
No, I can't... I can't believe
we're doing this again.

09:36.212 --> 09:38.746
- Yeah, I know.
- What do I tell the kids?

09:38.815 --> 09:41.048
The same thing you always tell them.

09:41.117 --> 09:43.150
You know, that mommy loves them so much,

09:43.219 --> 09:45.620
and three months isn't really that long.

09:45.688 --> 09:47.188
And what do I tell myself?

09:47.257 --> 09:49.490
That...

09:49.559 --> 09:51.659
you knew this was gonna
be a big part of our life

09:51.728 --> 09:53.394
when you married me.

09:53.463 --> 09:56.230
I gotta go.

10:16.619 --> 10:18.586
Thanks to Sergeant Roback here,

10:18.655 --> 10:20.755
Secretary Goodall
reached out to my office

10:20.823 --> 10:22.957
to go on a ride-along
with my flight medics,

10:23.026 --> 10:24.759
specifically your crew.

10:24.827 --> 10:26.294
I thought we were grounded, sir.

10:26.362 --> 10:28.229
You were, but against
my better judgment,

10:28.298 --> 10:29.830
I have no choice but to send you up.

10:29.899 --> 10:31.799
And if this was a ruse
to get reinstated,

10:31.868 --> 10:33.701
congratulations, it worked.

10:33.770 --> 10:35.570
But know that if I was not a crew short,

10:35.638 --> 10:36.958
you'd all still be on the ground.

10:36.973 --> 10:38.839
Life has a funny way of changing up

10:38.908 --> 10:41.108
- the best laid plans, sir.
- But some more than others.

10:41.109 --> 10:42.656
Just happy to be back in the air, sir.

10:42.657 --> 10:43.844
I'm sure you are.

10:43.913 --> 10:45.873
Does this mean that our
pay is being reinstated?

10:45.874 --> 10:47.214
It does.

10:47.283 --> 10:49.243
Can't send the Secretary
of the whole goddamn Army

10:49.285 --> 10:51.919
up with a crew who's serving
out an Article 15, can I?

10:51.988 --> 10:55.222
- Couldn't agree more, sir.
- Davis, you're dismissed.

10:55.291 --> 10:57.725
You two stay here.

10:57.794 --> 10:59.514
I've just received word
from Corporal Durkin

10:59.529 --> 11:01.129
that you've both been
given the green light

11:01.130 --> 11:02.698
for your Permanent
Resident Card interview.

11:02.699 --> 11:04.065
- Yes, sir.
- The corporal will RV

11:04.093 --> 11:05.693
with you both to schedule transportation

11:05.694 --> 11:07.068
to Bagram and the embassy.

11:07.136 --> 11:08.936
- Thank you, sir.
- We really appreciate this.

11:08.937 --> 11:10.237
Uh-huh.

11:10.306 --> 11:11.505
You don't understand.

11:11.574 --> 11:13.407
My mother has cancer,

11:13.476 --> 11:15.142
she's fighting for her life.

11:15.211 --> 11:17.812
My father has recently been
laid off from the factory

11:17.880 --> 11:19.614
where he worked for 35 years.

11:19.682 --> 11:22.516
They barely have enough money
for the both of them to eat,

11:22.585 --> 11:24.085
let alone to pay the mortgage

11:24.153 --> 11:26.954
and a mountain of medical bills.

11:27.924 --> 11:29.924
Yes, I understand that the hospital

11:29.993 --> 11:31.525
has a lien on the house,

11:31.594 --> 11:34.729
but my nephews and nieces
live in that house too.

11:35.498 --> 11:37.932
Taking that house away
means that you are putting

11:38.001 --> 11:40.668
three generations out on the street.

11:40.737 --> 11:44.739
Listen, I wish that I could
speak to you in person,

11:44.807 --> 11:47.108
but I'm currently stationed overseas.

11:48.511 --> 11:50.177
That's correct, sir.

11:50.246 --> 11:53.447
I'm in the United States Army.

11:53.516 --> 11:56.150
Thank you.

11:56.219 --> 12:00.354
Okay, I can get you $1,500
by the first of the month.

12:01.824 --> 12:04.025
All right, what's the total amount owed?

12:05.828 --> 12:08.362
$152,000?

12:08.431 --> 12:11.766
That's 12 grand more
than it was a month ago!

12:13.536 --> 12:15.369
Interest?

12:17.106 --> 12:21.709
Listen to me, you ice cold motherfucker,

12:21.778 --> 12:24.178
this is straight up goddamn robbery!

12:26.416 --> 12:29.050
I don't give a shit if this
call is being recorded!

12:29.118 --> 12:30.918
I'm glad it's being recorded!

12:30.987 --> 12:33.421
I want you to play it back
over and over again

12:33.489 --> 12:35.356
so you can be reminded of how deeply

12:35.425 --> 12:38.025
I'm gonna fuck you when
I get back stateside!

12:38.094 --> 12:40.394
Do you hear me? Hello?

12:44.934 --> 12:47.435
The hell y'all looking at?

12:53.936 --> 12:56.001
Hey, can we talk?

12:57.405 --> 12:59.205
Does it have anything
to do with the mission

12:59.206 --> 13:00.539
we're about to go on?

13:00.608 --> 13:02.608
Not exactly.

13:02.677 --> 13:04.176
Then no, we can't talk.

13:04.245 --> 13:06.178
This is just business hours only.

13:06.247 --> 13:08.114
Let me focus on my shit
and you focus on yours,

13:08.182 --> 13:10.015
and let's get this thing over with.

13:11.419 --> 13:13.953
- We're gonna fix this, amigo.
- You hear me?

13:18.292 --> 13:20.960
- Should I get you a vest too?
- No, thank you.

13:21.028 --> 13:22.862
Guessing you've been
through this before.

13:22.930 --> 13:25.631
That vest looks like it's been around.

13:25.700 --> 13:27.299
We, uh, we ready to go, fellas?

13:27.368 --> 13:28.934
Always ready, sir.

13:29.003 --> 13:32.238
- May I make one suggestion?
- Yeah, absolutely.

13:32.306 --> 13:34.266
You're the pros here. I'm
just along for the ride.

13:34.267 --> 13:35.841
Quick fashion tip for the next time

13:35.910 --> 13:38.344
you find yourself outside the wire,

13:38.412 --> 13:39.712
try wearing camouflage.

13:39.781 --> 13:41.447
Oxfords and chinos stand out.

13:41.516 --> 13:43.649
You don't wanna make
yourself an easy target.

13:43.718 --> 13:46.218
I told you, Ryan.

13:46.287 --> 13:47.887
He doesn't listen to anybody.

13:47.955 --> 13:49.822
Don't worry, we'll be up in the air,

13:49.891 --> 13:52.024
so if you die, we all die with you.

13:52.727 --> 13:56.662
Crash's sense of humor runs
a bit toward the dark side.

13:56.731 --> 13:59.064
They... they call you Crash?

13:59.133 --> 14:01.567
Interesting nickname for a pilot.

14:01.636 --> 14:03.903
Three tours, three crashes.

14:04.772 --> 14:06.572
Statistical anomaly.

14:31.966 --> 14:34.500
Oh, my goodness.

14:34.569 --> 14:36.902
How you holding up?

14:38.639 --> 14:42.474
We need to land this thing.
I gotta catch my breath.

14:42.543 --> 14:44.343
That's not really on the itinerary.

